The paper deals with optimizing the memory usage of Strassen-Winograd's matrix multiplication algorithm, which is a fundamental algorithm in computer science. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to algorithms and data structures, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Algebraic Manipulation). Additionally, the paper involves numerical computations and optimization, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
